  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will assess the efficacy of a new intradermal formulation of the trivalent
      inactivated influenza vaccine compared to the standard intramuscular vaccine in HIV-infected
      men who have sex with men in Bangkok, Thailand. Relative efficacy of the two different
      formulations of influenza vaccine will be assessed by comparing immunologic responses to
      vaccine between the two study arms.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
